President Muhammadu Buhari is currently receiving the report of the Presidential Advisory Committee on the New Minimum wage. The president had, on January 9, this year, constituted the panel, chaired by the Managing Director of the Financial Derivatives Company, Bismarck Rewane. The report of the 24-man panel is being presented at the council chambers of the State House, Abuja. Details soon. Minimum Wage: Panel submits report to Buhari, recommends N30,000 JUST IN: Minimum wage: Govs keep mum after meeting with Buhari Minimum Wage: Buhari, Governors in crucial meeting